      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(codex): honor node exec policy for native surfaces",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Keep Codex app-server native execution policy private to the bundled Codex plugin; this PR no longer adds or exports public plugin SDK APIs.\n- Disable app-server-owned native execution when the effective OpenClaw exec target resolves to `host=node`, including direct app-server execution methods, native compaction, `/btw`, native `/codex` command paths, and bound app-server conversation turns.\n- Preserve normal Codex harness turns by keeping OpenClaw `exec` / `process` available under `host=node`, while leaving the first-party CLI node binding path intact.\n\nFixes #85012\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/native-execution-policy.test.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/request.test.ts extensions/codex/src/conversation-binding.test.ts` (`28 passed`)\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 OPENCLAW_VITEST_FS_MODULE_CACHE_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-node-policy-pr-run-attempt node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts -t \"node-targeted Codex app-server runs|OpenClaw exec host=node is active\"` (`1 passed`, `208 skipped`)\n- AWS Crabbox fix proof and regression repro: provider `aws`, lease `cbx_4bba4b6a4708`, run `run_f344d939c79c`, exit `0`\n- `$autoreview` on the reshaped patch: clean, no actionable findings\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Codex app-server native execution surfaces no longer bypass OpenClaw `exec host=node`; node-targeted Codex harness turns keep OpenClaw shell tools so execution routes through OpenClaw instead of Codex native app-server execution.\n\nReal environment tested: Direct AWS Crabbox Linux environment, provider `aws`, lease `cbx_4bba4b6a4708`, run `run_f344d939c79c`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --provider aws --idle-timeout 90m --ttl 240m --timing-json --env-from-profile /private/tmp/iao.env --allow-env OPENAI_API_KEY --script-stdin` with a script that saved the local patch, reversed it to reproduce the pre-fix behavior, reapplied it, then ran the policy proof and focused regression tests.\n\nEvidence after fix: The regression half showed that without the patch, node-targeted runs still enabled the Codex native surface and a raw `command/exec` reached Codex native execution. After reapplying the patch, the same raw `command/exec` was blocked before app-server execution with the node-host policy message, and focused Codex policy tests passed.\n\nObserved result after fix: The proof printed `OPENCLAW_85012_CODEX_NODE_POLICY_CRABBOX_PROOF=passed`; the Crabbox run exited `0`.\n\nWhat was not tested: No real paired macOS node was attached for a full Linux-gateway-plus-macOS-node `Darwin` transcript. The proof verifies the broken app-server execution surface and the fixed OpenClaw block/reroute policy on live AWS Crabbox.\n",
        "branch": "fix/codex-node-native-policy-complete",
